Given the following program and the specified variable, optimize it out by constant propagation or copy propagation. If this variable is unused, just optimize it out.. The program is unsigned ac = 1;
int main() {
  short an = 0x294A;
  int tmp1 = ac || (an = 0);
  short ao = 0xBCD1;
  int tmp2 = ao - (1 - an);
  int tmp3 = tmp2 - tmp1 & 1;
  int v_int = tmp3;
  printf("checksum = %d\n", v_int);
  return 0;
}
.                 The target to be optimized is ao.
